The paper deals with detecting multiple accounts on social networks, specifically Facebook, which falls under the category of social networks (cs.SOC). The proposed approach involves using graph embedding and semi-supervised learning, which are techniques commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the importance of local information, which is a common theme in cybersecurity (cs.CR) and social network analysis (cs.SI).
